articles.title: Storm Boris: Polish city evacuates as floods batter central Europe - BBC.com
articles.description: Several people have died across the Czech Republic, Austria, Romania and Poland following devastating floods.
articles.content:
A flooded area in Nysa, Poland
The mayor of a Polish city has asked all 44,000 residents to evacuate, as widespread flooding continues to batter central Europe.

articles.title: Asia shares rise; dollar, yields hurt by outsized Fed rate cut bets - Reuters.com
articles.description: European stocks were higher on Tuesday, while the U.S. dollar was pinned lower, a day before the U.S. Federal Reserve is expected to begin an easing cycle that could see policymakers deliver an outsized rate cut.
